title: For Sale:  Taylor Fur Getter, .22 cal. single shot trap gun pat'd June 2, 1914
postcontent: F.C. Taylor Fur Getter, .22 LR caliber single shot pistol designed to shoot an animal at close range once the trigger mechanism has been activated. It was patented by C.D. Lovelace in June of 1914 under patent #1,098,742 and marketed under the name Taylor Fur Getter, F.C. Taylor Fur Co., St. Louis, MO. It was manufactured by O.F. Mossberg for Taylor. This gun is engraved with "TAYLOR FUR GETTER F.C. TAYLOR FUR CO. ST. LOUIS. MO" on the left side of the frame, and “PAT’D JUNE 2 1914 OTHER PAT'S PENDING" on the right side of the frame. Serial #2991 engraved on the frame and serial #3098 engraved on the barrel. Total length is 15-1/4” from end of bait hook to end of the cocking / retracting rod. The gun is 11-1/2” long including its 6” barrel. Gun height is 5-1/4” from top of frame to end of mounting screw. This gun has a brass barrel and brass frame. The bait hook, cocking / retracting rod and firing pin are steel as is the lower portion of the wood screw used for mounting. The Fur Getter was a purpose-designed “trap” gun, meant to shoot an animal in the face at point blank range. This was accomplished by mounting the gun to a tree or fence post with its 2-1/4" screw then connecting the firing mechanism to the bait hook, which extends 4" in front of the muzzle. The idea is that bait (usually raw meat) was placed on the hook and an animal grabs the bait and yanks on it, which pulls the trigger, which releases the firing pin mechanism. The gun fires at such close range that striking the animal and killing it is almost certain. This gun is in good condition with an attractive patina forming on the brass components. It has a few small areas of pitting on the steel parts. To my knowledge this gun is mechanically sound.

title: For Sale:  Bad s 300 WIN MAG-Picatinny forend rail
postcontent:
Noreen has created the ONLY SEMI-AUTOMATIC .300 WIN MAG and .338 Lapua on the market. The BAD NEWS is a custom-made AR-style rifle that is chambered in the increasingly popular 338 Lapua as well as the powerful 300 WIN MAG. These cartridges give you much greater velocity and power than the typical .308, and as far as ballistics are concerned, the BAD NEWS rifle is going to be the flatter shooting gun for long range shots.

The BAD NEWS rifle is a piston-driven semi-auto; this means you can expect greater range and a higher level of reliability by running a cleaner and cooler rifle. The muzzle break on these Noreen’s significantly suppresses recoil. Additionally, the semi-auto nature of the rifle will naturally recoil less than a bolt action because part of the felt recoil is going to chamber the next round. Lighter recoil is a huge advantage when you’re looking for a rifle with a faster and more accurate follow-up shot.

This piston-driven system is unlike any other AR-10 on the market. The piston movement is strictly in the action, after the bullet has already left the barrel. This is a huge advantage on a precision rifle compared to conventional piston driven setups found in standard AR's. In those rifles, an LWRC REPR, POF P308, etc. the piston runs parallel to the barrel and moves while the bullet is still in the barrel creating unwanted barrel harmonics which adversely affect accuracy. This rifle's piston is located in the receiver and not along the barrel so the bullet is out of the barrel by the time the piston is working to chamber another round and keep your action cool and clean with no gas ever entering the action.

The semi-automatic will not only give you a much faster follow-up shot, it also allows you to stay focused on your target, optic and the trigger, instead of having to manually operate a bolt-action rifle; all subsequent rounds are chambered by the rifle itself during the gas or blowback operation of the action.

The weapon easily disassembles like the standard AR for quick and easy cleaning and reassembly. The piston system drastically reduces fouling, and no venting means no holes for dirt and other contaminants to enter the system.

The full-length Picatinny rail on the receiver will allow you to mount scopes, lights, lasers, bipods, bayonets, etc. The adjustable cheek rest stock option is an added upgrade free bonus.

The innovative Noreen Bad News 300 WIN MAG provides tactical marksmen with the performance of a powerful and proven long range cartridge with the numerous advantages of the venerable AR platform. The Noreen 300 WIN MAG weighs only 13 pounds, and it vastly outperforms comparable bolt-action sniper rifles. This rifle comes with a custom muzzle-break and semi-auto action that significantly suppresses recoil. In the AR tradition, the Bad News 338 Lapua disassembles quickly for easy cleaning, then reasembles with no loss of zero. The familiar fit and feel of a conventional AR rifle makes the transition to the more powerful sniper rifle seamless. This Noreen includes an ultra-heavy duty Plano case, which is far superior to a pelican style case. 100% Made in the USA.

www.onlylongrange.com

title: For Sale:  Guns For Sale - Colt -- SAA,.45, San Jacinto,Special Edition W/Walnut Case
postcontent:
Unfired, cylinder unturned. Special edition, one of 200. Commemorates the Battle of San Jacinto. 7.5" barrel. Walnut grips. Cylinder depicts Sam Houston and Santa Ana, along with related images. Engraving on both sides of the frame and on the backstrap. "The Battle of San Jacinto, April 21, 1836" is engraved on the barrel right side. Left side barrel is engraved "Remember the Alamo - Remember Goliad." The walnut presentation case is lined in red velvet and bears a plaque with images of Sam Houston and Santa Ana on top of the locking lid. The key is missing as are the factory papers. The finish is so highly reflective that it was very hard to photograph. Questions or requests for additional photographs are always welcomed. Will accept lay-away.
